The '''Torresian kingfisher''' ('''''Todiramphus sordidus''''') is a species of bird in the family [[Alcedinidae]].  It is found in southern [[New Guinea]] and in Australia. Its natural [[habitat]]s are subtropical or tropical moist lowland forests, mangroves, and [[plantation]]s.  It was formerly considered a subspecies of the [[collared kingfisher]].

==Taxonomy==
Three subspecies are recognised:<ref>Gill, F. and D. Donsker, eds. (2020). ''IOC World Bird List (v 10.1).'' Doi 10.14344/IOC.ML.10.1.  https://www.worldbirdnames.org/ioc-lists/master-list-2/</ref>

* ''T. s. sordidus'' (Gould, 1842) – [[Aru Islands]], southern coasts of New Guinea, and northern and north-eastern coasts of Australia<ref name=Woodall></ref>
* ''T. s. pilbara'' (Johnstone, 1983) – coastal north-western Australia from the [[De Grey River]] to [[Exmouth Gulf]]<ref name=Woodall>Woodall, P. F. (2020). "Torresian Kingfisher (Todiramphus sordidus), version 1.0." In ''Birds of the World'' (S. M. Billerman, B. K. Keeney, P. G. Rodewald, and T. S. Schulenberg, Editors). Cornell Lab of Ornithology, Ithaca, NY, USA. https://doi.org/10.2173/bow.colkin9.01</ref> 
* ''T. s. colcloughi'' (Mathews, 1916) – coastal east central to southeastern [[Queensland]]<ref name=Woodall></ref>

